IMAGE;VALUE=URI;DISPLAY=BADGE;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://buffalobayou.org/w
 p-content/uploads/2023/04/Waugh-Bridge-Bat-Colony-1-1.jpg
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://buffalobayou.org/wp-content/uploads/2023/
 04/Waugh-Bridge-Bat-Colony-1-1.jpg
UID:kTQU_yvXeUdh-pA7tkEsg
SUMMARY:Bat Chat
DTSTAMP:20260616T174855Z
DTSTART:20260626T193000Z
DESCRIPTION:Stroll to Waugh Drive Bridge for a Bat Chat with the Houston Ar
	ea Bat Team and see the bat colony up close! \nDid you know? These populat
	ion of Mexican Free-tailed Bats at the Waugh Bridge can reach a peak of ap
	proximately 300\,000 in the summer months! Around sunset\, the colony leav
	es the crevices beneath the bridge and create a whirlwind-like formation a
	s they emerge. Join the Houston Area Bat Team to learn and discover as the
	y share fun\, educational facts and insights about these miniature\, flyin
	g mammals! \nInvite your family and friends\, bring a picnic blanket\, wea
	r your bug spray\, and admire this unique phenomena. \n\n\n\nBat Chats are
	 held every Friday evening from May to August as part of our Summer Specie
	s series\, starting 30 minutes before sunset. \n  \nCost\nFree \nTime\n7:3
	0 – 8:30pm (30 minutes before sunset) \nMeeting Location\nWaugh Bridge Bat
	 Colony Observation Deck (along Allen Parkway) \nREGISTRATION\n\nhttps://b
	uffalobayou.org/event/2026-june-bat-chat-4/\n\nFrom Buffalo Bayou Partners
	hip
URL:https://buffalobayou.org/event/2026-june-bat-chat-4/
LOCATION:Waugh Drive Bat Bridge\, 1
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:buffalo-bayou-partnership
CATEGORIES:Buffalo Bayou Partnership
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
IMAGE;VALUE=URI;DISPLAY=BADGE;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://houstonarboretum.or
 g/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Phenology-1280-x-720.png
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://houstonarboretum.org/wp-content/uploads/20
 26/05/Phenology-1280-x-720.png
UID:GZCSCo5xnN2BMTKXp8cVf
SUMMARY:Fourth Saturday Phenology Walk
DTSTAMP:20260616T174855Z
DTSTART:20260627T090000Z
DESCRIPTION:Fourth Saturday of the Month9:00 – 11:00 amFree\, donations app
	reciatedAll ages\, minors must be accompanied by an adult \n\n\n\nMeet in 
	front of the Nature Center building \n\n\n\nDiscover the hidden seasonal r
	hythms of nature firsthand on our guided Phenology Walks\, where we track 
	the life cycles of different plants across ecosystems\, from the first spr
	ing bud burst to winter dormancy. You’ll learn how shifting weather patter
	ns and climate change influence the timing of these important events in ou
	r local ecosystems and how you can become a community scientist\, contribu
	ting vital data from your own backyard to a global research initiative.  \
	n\n\n\nThese relaxing morning walks are led by scientists from Rice Univer
	sity and staff from the Arboretum. We welcome nature enthusiasts of all ag
	es\, however kids 12 years and younger must be accompanied by a guardian. 
	\n\n\n\nLearn more about the study of phenology and ways you can contribut
	e at https://www.usanpn.org/nn \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nCommunity Science Partner\n
	\nhttps://houstonarboretum.org/event/fourth-saturday-phenology-walk/2026-0
	6-27/\n\nFrom Houston Arboretum & Nature Center
URL:https://houstonarboretum.org/event/fourth-saturday-phenology-walk/2026-
	06-27/
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:houston-arboretum
CATEGORIES:Houston Arboretum & Nature Center
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
